    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-04T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="767"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/2050</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-04T21:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1918, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 5, 4 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5706. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1"
                        >McFadden</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 567. We are advised by Madrid: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>A.E.F. have purchased or contracted for 47,500 Spanish mules. Prior to
                            first November export permits covering 10,000 had been granted by
                            Spanish Government.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>On 2d November Spanish Government authorized export of 25,000
                            additional and permits covering same will be immediately provided War
                            Trade Board. Total export mules authorized will then be 35,000.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>In addition thereto A.E.F. have purchased in Portugal 15,000 Spanish
                            mules which Spanish Government have authorized transmit by rail through
                            Spain and to France.</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>Position is A.E.F. have purchased or contracted for 47,500 mules
                            against which export permits have been secured for 35,000 and the right
                            of transit through Spain for 15,000 additional from Portugal. We are not
                            yet informed as to compensations given by War Trade Board to Spanish
                            Government in consideration thereof.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>A.E.F. desire us to express to State Department and War Trade Board their
                    appreciation of your efforts and support in securing export permits covering
                    these animals. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1"
                    >McFadden</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
